.SH EMULATORS 
The program supports many type of emulators. The emulators
AdvanceMAME, AdvanceMESS, MAME, xmame, DMAME,
DMESS and DRAINE are directly supported and the only thing
you should do is to run the AdvanceMENU program in the same
directory of the emulator.
.PP
All the other emulators are supported with the emulator
type \(oqgeneric\(cq.
.SS generic \(hy Generic emulator 
For the \(oqgeneric\(cq emulator no additional rom information is
needed. Only the name and the size of the rom files are used.
.PP
You should specify all emulator information and directories
with the \(oqemulator\(cq and \(oqemulator_*\(cq options in the
\(oqadvmenu.rc\(cq file.
.PP
You need to use at least the \(oqemulator\(cq and \(oqemulator_roms\(cq
options to inform AdvanceMENU how to run the emulator and where
to find the roms.
.PP
For example:
.PP
.RS 4
emulator \(a"snes9x\(a" generic \(a"c:\(rsgame\(rssnes9x\(rssnes9x.exe\(a" \(a"%f\(a"
.PD 0
.PP
.PD
emulator_roms \(a"snes9x\(a" \(a"c:\(rsgame\(rssnes9x\(rsroms\(a"
.PD 0
.PP
.PD
emulator_roms_filter \(a"snes9x\(a" \(a"*.smc;*.sfc;*.fig;*.1\(a"
.PD 0
.PP
.PD
.RE
.PP
.RS 4
emulator \(a"zsnes\(a" generic \(a"c:\(rsgame\(rszsnes\(rszsnes.exe\(a" \(a"\(hye \(hym roms\(rs%f\(a"
.PD 0
.PP
.PD
emulator_roms \(a"zsnes\(a" \(a"c:\(rsgame\(rszsnes\(rsroms\(a"
.PD 0
.PP
.PD
emulator_roms_filter \(a"zsnes\(a" \(a"*.smc;*.sfc;*.fig;*.1\(a"
.PD 0
.PP
.PD
.RE
.PP
The various %s, %f, %p, ... macros are explained in the \(oqemulator\(cq
option description.
.PP
The roms are searched in the path specified with the
\(oqemulator_roms\(cq option in the \(oqadvmenu.rc\(cq file. For every file
found (with any extension) a game is added in the menu.
You can filter the files with the \(oqemulator_roms_filter\(cq option.
.PP
All the snapshots are searched in the directories specified with
the \(oqemulator_*\(cq options using the same name of the rom file.
.PP
If you want, you can manually write a MAME like information file
and name it as \(oqENUNAME.lst\(cq. This file has the same format
of the output of the \(oq\(hylistinfo\(cq MAME command.
Actually only the information \(oqgame\(cq, \(oqname\(cq, \(oqdescription\(cq, \(oqyear\(cq,
\(oqmanufacturer\(cq, \(oqcloneof\(cq are used.
Please note that this file is used only to add information at the
existing games. The games present in this file are not automatically
added at the game list.
.SS advmame \(hy AdvanceMAME 
For the \(oqadvmame\(cq emulator type the roms informations are
gathered from the file \(oqENUNAME.xml\(cq. If this file doesn\(cqt
exist, it\(cqs created automatically with emulator \(oq\(hylistxml\(cq
command.
.PP
The directories specified in the \(oqdir_rom\(cq option in the
\(oqadvmame.rc\(cq file are used to detect the list of the
available roms. In the DOS and Windows versions of the
program the \(oqadvmenu.rc\(cq file is searched in the same directory
of the emulator. In the Unix version it\(cqs searched in the
\(oqHOME/.advance\(cq directory.
.PP
The directory specified in \(oqdir_snap\(cq is used to
detect the list of available snapshots.
.SS advmess \(hy AdvanceMESS 
For the \(oqadvmess\(cq emulator the rom information is gathered
from the file \(oqEMUNAME.xml\(cq. If this file doesn\(cqt exist,
it\(cqs created automatically with emulator \(oq\(hylistxml\(cq command.
.PP
The directories specified in the \(oqdir_rom\(cq option in the
\(oqadvmess.rc\(cq file are used to detect the list of the
available bioses.
.PP
All the directories listed in the option \(oqdir_image\(cq are
read and all the files found in the \(oqmachine\(cq directories
are inserted as software if the extension is recognized as a
valid device extension for the current \(oqmachine\(cq or if it\(cqs a
\(oqzip\(cq file.
For example if the \(oqdir_image\(cq options is \(oqc:\(rssoftware\(cq,
AdvanceMENU scans the directories \(oqc:\(rssoftware\(rsti99_4a\(cq,
\(oqc:\(rssoftware\(rssms\(cq, \(oqc:\(rssoftware\(rsgameboy\(cq...
Files in the main directory \(oqc:\(rssoftware\(cq are NOT checked.
.PP
When you select to run a zip file, the zip file is opened and
all the files in the zip with a valid name and with a recognized
device extension are added at the AdvanceMESS command line.
A file is considered to have a valid name if has the same name
of the zip of if it has the name of the zip with an additional
char. For example in the file \(oqalpiner.zip\(cq the files
\(oqalpiner.bin\(cq, \(oqalpinerc.bin\(cq and \(oqalpinerg.bin\(cq have a valid
name. This feature can be used to group all the required roms
to play a software in a single zip file.
.PP
The file extension is also used to correctly select the device
type when calling AdvanceMESS.
.PP
The directory specified in \(oqdir_snap\(cq is used to detect the
list of available snapshots.
At any exit of AdvanceMESS if a new snapshot is created, this
file is moved to the correct \(oqsnap\(rssystem\(cq directory renaming
it as the software started.
For example, suppose that you run the \(oqti99_4a\(cq system with the
software \(oqalpiner\(cq. If you press F12 during the emulation, the
file \(oqsnap\(rsti99_4a.png\(cq is created. When you return to
AdvanceMENU the file is moved automatically to
\(oqsnap\(rsti99_4a\(rsalpiner.png\(cq.
