.SH CONFIGURATION 
The file \(oqadvmenu.rc\(cq is used to save the current state of the
front\(hyend. It\(cqs read at startup and saved at exit. You can
prevent the automatic save at the exit with the \(oqconfig\(cq option.
.PP
In DOS and Windows the configuration options are read from the
file \(oqadvmenu.rc\(cq in the current directory.
.PP
In Linux and Mac OS X the configuration options are read from the
files \(oqadvmame.rc\(cq and \(oqadvmess.rc\(cq in the $host, $data and
the $home directory.
The $host directory is \(oq$SYSCONFDIR\(cq, where $SYSCONFDIR is the
\(oqsysconfdir\(cq directory configured with the \(oqconfigure\(cq script.
The default is \(oq/usr/local/etc\(cq.
The $data directory is \(oq$DATADIR/advance\(cq, where $DATADIR is the
\(oqdatadir\(cq directory configured with the \(oqconfigure\(cq script.
The default is \(oq/usr/local/share\(cq.
The $home directory is \(oq$ADVANCE\(cq, where $ADVANCE is the value of the
ADVANCE environment variable when the program is run.
If the ADVANCE environment variable is missing the $home directory
is \(oq$HOME/.advance\(cq where $HOME is the value of the HOME environment
variable.
If both the ADVANCE and HOME environment variables are missing the
$data directory became also the $home directory.
.PP
The priority of the options is in the order: $host, $home and $data.
.PP
The $home directory is also used to write all the information
by the program. The files in the $host and $data directory are only read.
.PP
You can include an additional configuration files with the \(oqinclude\(cq
option. In DOS and Windows the files are searched in the current directory.
In Linux and Mac OS X the files are searched in the $home directory if
they are expressed as a relative path. You can force the search in the
current directory prefixing the file with \(oq./\(cq.
To include more than one file you must divide the names with \(oq;\(cq in
DOS and Windows, and with \(oq:\(cq in Linux and Mac OS X.
.PP
You can force the creation of a default configuration file with the
command line option \(oq\(hydefault\(cq.
.PP
In DOS and Windows the directory name separator is \(oq\(rs\(cq and the
multi\(hydirectory separator is \(oq;\(cq. In Linux and Mac OS X the directory
name separator is \(oq/\(cq and the multi\(hydirectory separator is \(oq:\(cq.
.SS Global Configuration Options 
This section describes the global options used to
customize the the program.
.PP
A subset of the configuration options are saved per
emulator basis to allow different configurations for
different emulators. Please note that these specific emulator
configurations are not activated if you select to show
more than one emulator at time.
In this case only the default configuration is used.
Specifically these special options are \(oqmode\(cq, \(oqsort\(cq,
\(oqpreview\(cq, \(oqgroup_include\(cq and \(oqtype_include\(cq.
.SS config 
Selects if and when the configuration modified by the user at
runtime should be saved.
.PP
